m. But the other sister, as I say, she was - living in this hotel - barmaid. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 So there was just the family there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Did she do all her own washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Did she make any clothes for you - anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Well - sh
e used to make - some of the clothes but in those days - we - tell you the truth I've gone all over the place cadging clothes from different ones. Anyone as had anything to - to spare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Did your dad ever cobble shoes or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Any wh
at? Oh yes, he used to do those - get - he had a last and he used to repair the - but as I said they was all clogs. He used to put the irons on the clogs and that you know and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Your father put leather between the irons to save the irons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Yes. To save the irons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Do you remember any particular time of the year you got clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 
Well we was - you was very lucky if you got any new suits or anything of that at Whit week. You used to get other people's cast offs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 But most people did wear new clothes at Whit week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 
Oh yes. Oh yes, there was always - was always Whit week when you - was all dressed up.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Did your father help with jobs around the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 My father never helped in anything. He was that strict, I'll tell y
ou, he used to sit there reading the paper with his feet on the oven door and if you wanted to pass to go to the cupboard we had to climb underneath his legs to go to the cupboard. He was that strict and if you was playing in the house and he made any - m
ade any noise or anything he used to say - oh. Never used to speak - used to point upstairs and we knew I had to go. That was it. That was discipline.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Did you do any jobs around the house to help your mum?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Oh I - I done everything in the house. T
hat was why I was so handy when I come to be on me own. I've had to scrub floors, help to wash and clean. I've - I've baked many a two dozen of bread. Yes, I've baked bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 What about the other children - did they help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 They - this as I come al
ong when I was getting say eleven and twelve and such as - round about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 What time did you have to go to bed in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Oh, seven - just after tea every night we had to be in bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Who put you to bed when you were tiny - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Oh, we had to go to bed ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 When you were too tiny to put yourself to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 
Oh - was elder sisters and - brother - that was older than me used to look after me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 They helped you dress and undress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Did you ever do anything back for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Oh all - I suppose I did in - in the younger days - I did eventually.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 
When you were a child do you remember - no? How often did you bath and where did you bath - how many times did you have clean clothes on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 I 
used to have a proper bath - see as how we used to have to go to the public baths. Openshaw public baths. But - as a young - I can't remember, 'cos we hadn't a bath at all you see. Used to have to get a tin bath out an the hearth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Where did the family
 have their meals in the two roomed house and where did you mum cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 
Well there was only four rooms - there were only a little kitchen, little back kitchen where mother did the cooking on the stove and - the old fashioned oven. - The gas stove and the old fashioned - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15223\charrsid16603783 gate}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783  oven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 
Can you tell me about breakfast - did you all eat together? Do you remember how many were present at breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 
Well I - as I say, there's only - these four as I can really remember at home. Oh five - Ernest, he - he left home when he was about sixteen or seventeen. He was really the main wage earner at that time. Now -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 What did he do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 
He was a moulder. Now - he's - he was the main wage earner and I've seen him come home, I remember him coming home from wo
rk on a Saturday and he's taken his clothes off and gone and had a bath. Me mother's taken his working clothes to pawn and she's pawned them to get his suit out to go out for weekend and he used to wear his suit for weekend and then she used to pawn his S
unday - Monday morning at half past five when used to get up and take his best suit back to pawn to get his working clothes out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Do you remember anything about the pawn shops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Yes. Yes. Arden's pawn shop and Ashton Old Road. They used to go in t
he little back entry into the pledge office and the women used to queue up on the Monday morning - half past five to six o'clock - for him opening. Those days you could pawn anything. 'Cos they used to - they used to pawn them and what they call - so many
 days because they had to pay the month's interest and then get it out again. Paying through the eyes and nose. With interest and pawning a thing one week and the getting it out the next.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Do you remember the pattern of eating your house - what kind of 
food you ate in those days - what did you have for breakfast for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Oh we was very lucky if we got anything kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Tell me about your breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 
Well - breakfast really as I say were - you used to get - all as we got was a cup of tea and - bread and margarine or such as that. Lucky if you got jam on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 What about dinners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 
Oh - dinners - mother used to get bones from the butchers and - barley and carrots and such as that. Used to make a - a big pan of broth and soup. Yes. That's what we mostly lived on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Was Sunday a special day for food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 
Well that was a great - that was a great - shall we say great - great change if you got something such as that. Speaking about breakfast, if me father was having eggs all
 as we got was the top off the egg. The top - no - he used to just cut the top off and we had to be satisfied with the top of the egg and he had the egg.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 He got more because he was the worker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Did you ever see your mum going short so t
hat you as children could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 
Oh yes, she has many a time. I'll tell you what we - we have had is - young like that. Tuppeny packet of rice boiled in water and that was rice pudding. Really as a lad until I was about twelve years of age and th
en got working. Then - as I say, after me father went away - gradually built up but I was very thin and delicate always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 You think this was because of the food do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 
It was through lack of food as a child. That was how me brothers and sisters all used to leave home. Any food - any of - all the best food there was in the house father had it and we had to have what was left kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Your mum did bake you told me and you baked too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Did she make jam and pickles and thi
ngs like that or brew beer or make medicine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 
No, she didn't do anything like that - she used to just bake the bread. Bake bread and we used to have that. Bread and margarine or bread and dripping, whatever was going kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 You wouldn't be able to grow vegetables would you in Openshaw?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 
Oh yes. One - later on me father had an allotment. He an allotment in Abbeyhay.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 So he grew his own vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Oh he grew some of his own vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 Did he have any livestock at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 
Me and me - me and me - no - it was only a small allotment. Me and me brother, when we got - when I got a bit older than that, we used to go and do all the weeding and the turning over of the garden and all that sort of thing. And then at the Sunday 
morning when it was a case of - people going round buying the flowers and such as that me father used to go up and collect all the money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4129778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 He used to sell flowers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1853741 MS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14485215\charrsid16603783 
He - yes. We use - we used to - gon - it's quite all right. I mentioned - it doesn
't matter. Now I remember I used to run errands for - quite - when I was quite young - used to run errands for a lady and - all her errands for the week and go for her coal, in those days, you used to have to go to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
